# Cursor security preflight (federation)

When adopting tools, enabling third-party Cursor skills/MCP, or the user asks to harden Cursor configs:

1. Prefer the **federation** scanner (all Open Folder roots), not a single-repo script:
   ```bash
   cursor-security-preflight
   # or: bash "/Users/claudiobarone/Projects/Cemini claude code CCC/scripts/cursor_security_preflight_federation.sh"
   ```
2. Single workspace only when explicitly scoped:
   ```bash
   cursor-security-preflight --local
   cursor-security-preflight --root "/path/to/repo"
   ```
3. Reports: `~/.cursor/security-preflight/latest/` (gitignored home cache).
4. After editing federation skills in CCC, re-sync then re-scan:
   ```bash
   bash "/Users/claudiobarone/Projects/Cemini claude code CCC/scripts/sync_federation_cursor_skills.sh"
   cursor-security-preflight --quick
   ```

Agent runs this (not the user) for Cursor-related security checks. Summarize HIGH/CRITICAL findings; do not silently ignore CRITICAL.
